org.apache.flink.runtime.instance

类 SlotSharingGroupAssignment

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.flink.runtime.instance.SlotSharingGroupAssignment

  • public class SlotSharingGroupAssignment
extends java.lang.Object
    The SlotSharingGroupAssignment manages a set of shared slots, which are shared between tasks of a SlotSharingGroup.

    The assignments shares tasks by allowing a shared slot to hold one vertex per JobVertexID. For example, consider a program consisting of job vertices "source", "map", "reduce", and "sink". If the slot sharing group spans all four job vertices, then each shared slot can hold one parallel subtask of the source, the map, the reduce, and the sink vertex. Each shared slot holds the actual subtasks in child slots, which are (at the leaf level), the SimpleSlots.

    An exception are the co-location-constraints, that define that the i-th subtask of one vertex needs to be scheduled strictly together with the i-th subtasks of the vertices that share the co-location-constraint. To manage that, a co-location-constraint gets its own shared slot inside the shared slots of a sharing group.

    Consider a job set up like this:

    
 +-------------- Slot Sharing Group --------------+
 |                                                |
 |            +-- Co Location Group --+           |
 |            |                       |           |
 |  (source) ---> (head) ---> (tail) ---> (sink)  |
 |            |                       |           |
 |            +-----------------------+           |
 +------------------------------------------------+

    The slot hierarchy in the slot sharing group will look like the following

         Shared(0)(root)
        |
        +-- Simple(2)(sink)
        |
        +-- Shared(1)(co-location-group)
        |      |
        |      +-- Simple(0)(tail)
        |      +-- Simple(1)(head)
        |
        +-- Simple(0)(source)

      • getSlotForTask

        public SimpleSlot getSlotForTask(JobVertexID vertexID,
                                 java.lang.Iterable<TaskManagerLocation> locationPreferences)
        Gets a slot suitable for the given task vertex. This method will prefer slots that are local (with respect to ExecutionVertex.getPreferredLocationsBasedOnInputs()), but will return non local slots if no local slot is available. The method returns null, when this sharing group has no slot is available for the given JobVertexID.
        参数:
        vertexID - the vertex id
        locationPreferences - location preferences
        返回:
        A slot to execute the given ExecutionVertex in, or null, if none is available.

      • getSlotForTask

        public SimpleSlot getSlotForTask(CoLocationConstraint constraint,
                                 java.lang.Iterable<TaskManagerLocation> locationPreferences)
        Gets a slot for a task that has a co-location constraint. This method tries to grab a slot form the location-constraint's shared slot. If that slot has not been initialized, then the method tries to grab another slot that is available for the location-constraint-group.

        In cases where the co-location constraint has not yet been initialized with a slot, or where that slot has been disposed in the meantime, this method tries to allocate a shared slot for the co-location constraint (inside on of the other available slots).

        If a suitable shared slot is available, this method allocates a simple slot within that shared slot and returns it. If no suitable shared slot could be found, this method returns null.

        参数:
        constraint - The co-location constraint for the placement of the execution vertex.
        locationPreferences - location preferences
        返回:
        A simple slot allocate within a suitable shared slot, or null, if no suitable shared slot is available.
